/* This module contains procedures to scan off the command line arguments.  from the MONITOR.  It contains:..  SETUP_ARGS (progname):.     This procedure strips the program name (or command name) off the command.     line and sets things up so NEXT_ARG can strip off the command arguments..     It returns TRUE if the program was initiated via the RUN command and.     FALSE otherwise.  The following examples demonstrate what PROGNAME.     and the returned RUN flag are in various situations...     command line                  progname     run flag.     ------------                  --------     --------.     compare x y                   compare      false.     run compare x y               compare      true.     old compare;run               run          true.     old compare;com               com          false.     new j;pla bach13              pla          false..  NEXT_ARG (arg):.     This procedure returns the next command line argument in ARG (it.     also returns a pointer to ARG).  SETUP_ARGS must be called before.     this procedure.*/library ':-xpl:libs:scanargs'; /* get module */dcl setup_args proc(fixed array) returns (boolean) external; /* setup to get command line arguments */dcl next_arg   proc(fixed array) returns (pointer) external; /* get next command line argument */